  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently the ABI allows tuples to have 0 members and fixed length arrays to be at fixed 0 length.\r\n\r\n> The following (fixed-size) array type exists:\r\n> `<type>[M]`: a fixed-length array of `M` elements, `M >= 0`, of the given type.\r\n\r\nand\r\n\r\n> `(T1,T2,...,Tn)`: tuple consisting of the types `T1, â€¦, Tn`, `n >= 0`\r\n\r\nI am not convinced it makes sense supporting these.\r\n\r\nWhat are the arguments for having these?",
